-- Dunkin' Brands to sell Coca-Cola drinks
-- 
-- Mon Apr 2, 2012 6:36pm EDT
-- http://www.reuters.com/article/2012/04/02/us-dunkinbrands-idUSBRE83115Q20120402

 

 (Reuters) - Dunkin' Brands Group Inc ( DNKN.O ) will soon start serving Coca-Cola Co ( KO.N ) soft drinks at its Dunkin' Donuts cafes and Baskin-Robbins ice cream shops, the companies said on Monday. 
 Under the terms of their deal, more than 9,400 Dunkin' Donuts and Baskin-Robbins restaurants across the United States will begin selling Coke products, including juices, enhanced waters and energy drinks, by August. Shares of Coca-Cola were trading at $73.91 on Monday morning on the New York Stock Exchange, while those of Dunkin' were up 1 percent at $30.40 on the Nasdaq. (Reporting by Arpita Mukherjee in Bangalore; Editing by Viraj Nair)